{"parse":{"title":"Rigwnai","pageid":6154514,"revid":847057623,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Unreferenced\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>does not <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">cite</a> any <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rigwnai&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\" title=\"Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1\">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">removed</a>.</span>  <small><i>(December 2009)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Risa01.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7c/Risa01.jpg/250px-Risa01.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"175\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7c/Risa01.jpg/375px-Risa01.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7c/Risa01.jpg/500px-Risa01.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"420\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Risa01.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A pattern of rigwnai worn by the <a href=\"/wiki/Debbarma\" title=\"Debbarma\">Debbarmas</a>. Picture by Pankaj Debbarma</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Risa02.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/17/Risa02.jpg/250px-Risa02.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"340\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/17/Risa02.jpg/375px-Risa02.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/17/Risa02.jpg/500px-Risa02.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"816\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Risa02.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Another beautiful pattern of rigwnai of the <a href=\"/wiki/Debbarma\" title=\"Debbarma\">Debbarmas</a>. Picture by Pankaj Debbarma</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Rigwnai</b> is a wrap-around worn by <a href=\"/wiki/Tripuri_dress\" title=\"Tripuri dress\">Tripuri</a> women.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg/220px-A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"383\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg/330px-A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg/440px-A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2370\" data-file-height=\"4128\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_tripuri_girl_wearing_Rigwnai_and_Risa.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A young Tripuri woman wearing rigwnai and risa</div></div></div>\n<p>Rigwnai is the traditional dress of Tripuri women, the indigenous inhabitants of Tripura. It is similar to the traditional dresses of other indigenous communities in the north-eastern Indian states of <a href=\"/wiki/Assam\" title=\"Assam\">Assam</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Manipur\" title=\"Manipur\">Manipur</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Meghalaya\" title=\"Meghalaya\">Meghalaya</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Mizoram\" title=\"Mizoram\">Mizoram</a>, etc like the Indigenous <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Assamese_communities&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Assamese communities (page does not exist)\">Assamese communities</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mizo_communities&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Mizo communities (page does not exist)\">Mizo communities</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Naga_communities&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Naga communities (page does not exist)\">Naga communities</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hajong_communities&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Hajong communities (page does not exist)\">Hajong communities</a> etc. It is worn by wrapping it around the waist. Sometimes it is worn with \"risa\" which is a piece of cloth wrapped around the bust. It is mostly worn by the \"debbarma\" tribes and by other tribes in Tripura. A similar kind of rigwnai is worn by Manipuris and Mizos.\n</p><p>The most common kind of rigwnai is called the \"Chamathwi bar\" and comprises white cloth bordered by maroon or other colors. The \"Chamathwi bar\" is worn during important occasions like wedding ceremonies and festivals like Goria Puja and Hangrai.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rigwnai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Pathin\" title=\"Pathin\">Pathin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tripuri_people\" title=\"Tripuri people\">Tripuri people</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tripuri_Dances\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tripuri Dances\">Tripuri Dances</a></li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_India.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/25px-Flag_of_India.svg.png\" width=\"25\" height=\"17\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/38px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/50px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1350\" data-file-height=\"900\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about the culture of India is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rigwnai&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:India-culture-stub\" title=\"Template:India-culture-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:India-culture-stub\" title=\"Template talk:India-culture-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abb